                            <comment id="17772614" author="tilman" created="Fri, 6 Oct 2023 15:33:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve improved the log message and upgraded it to a warning. This might not really help you because increasing that value comes as a memory cost that is probably 4 x value&#178;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17772648" author="JIRAUSER302151" created="Fri, 6 Oct 2023 17:19:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks a lot &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; for helping with this.&lt;br/&gt;
If pdfbox.rendering.tilingpaint.maxedge property to 7000 will increase the memory usage significantly, then are there any other work arounds or suggesstions to improve this?&lt;br/&gt;
Also, are there any resources on how to estimate the memory usage for PDFBox operations in general?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17772650" author="tilman" created="Fri, 6 Oct 2023 17:33:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No there no other ideas. And there are no resources on how to estimate the memory usage.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17772651" author="JIRAUSER302151" created="Fri, 6 Oct 2023 17:36:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Got it, thank you!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
